rComments: The professor as a person is great, funny, chill and seems like a good guy. But the course is just a mess overall. He tested us on 5 chapters despite only teaching us about two. The TAs seem to be all over the place. His assignments are also very vague and the TAs are strict graders so getting a good grade on his assignments is virtually impossible

rComments: Hilarious and super laid back. Passionate about the course content, listens to his students' feedback and opinions. Tests are hard but he gives out extra credit. Make sure you do your readings and take good notes! The MCQ is a pain.

Honestly didn't know professors like this existed. After taking this class, I've tried my best to take any class that he offers. This sounds sarcastic but he literally is the best professor I've ever had. Super down to earth, hilarious, and very helpful if you speak to him. Go to office hours and he will always be more than happy to help!
Hes very funny, related alot of content to current events. The test are weighted pretty heavy. the readings are important and if you miss even one class youll be in trouble.

rComments: Great course but did not learn anything new. You have to be in class everyday and insure that you participate. I do not recommend this professor duo to the low consideration for special request. Also, his class has alternative way of teaching that requires the students to do more work on average than other classes.

He's a chill dude, not too hard to understand but his lectures are a mess. I recommend studying off the readings because we barely got through the lecture slides. Also the TAs didn't really know what was going on. Tests were okay, but he does offer extra credit.
